<TITLE> Italy's Panucci injured in training </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MOEDLING, Austria, June 7 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Italy defender Christian Panucci limped out of training on Friday after tweaking a tendon in his right knee. An Italian soccer federation statement said the 35-year-old returned to the dressing room only as a precaution. If fit, Panucci looks certain to play at right back for the world champions in their Euro 2008 Group C opener against Netherlands in Berne on Monday. Fellow defender Fabio Cannavaro was ruled out of the tournament earlier this week after tearing ankle ligaments during Italy's first training session in Austria. In an 11-a-side training game, Marco Materazzi and Andrea Barzagli played at centre back in one team as coach Roberto Donadoni assessed his option
